---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { site } from '../data/siteData.js';
---
<BaseLayout title={'About ' + site.business} description={site.business + ' is a Frederick-focused local service brand built around clear planning and dependable execution.'} canonicalPath="/about/">
  <section class="page-head"><h1>About {site.business}</h1><p>{site.sub}</p></section>
  <section class="section article"><p>{site.business} helps Frederick property owners get a fence plan that makes sense before posts are set, panels are ordered, or gates are placed. We look at the yard, the line, the grade, the access, and the reason the fence is being built.</p><p>Our first step is not pressure. We ask what the fence needs to solve: privacy, containment, safety, pool code, rental-property control, curb appeal, repair, replacement, or a cleaner boundary between neighbors.</p><p>Frederick properties vary widely, from historic homes and compact townhome lots to newer subdivisions, rural parcels, HOA communities, and small commercial buildings. A useful fence plan has to account for those conditions before materials, labor, and timing are finalized.</p></section>
</BaseLayout>
